            <div id="1p" class="text 1t">
                <h1>Registration on the platform</h1>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>Self-register at <a href=“https://openedu.ru”>openedu.ru<a>, then go to the section «Профиль».</p>
                    <img src="openedu/1.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <img src="openedu/2.png" width="400">
                    <p>Enter your surname, first name and middle name as they appear on your student ID card. The e-mail address must belong to the urfu.me.
                        <span class="bold">!Important: If you already have an account on openedu with a personal email from another domain, you need to edit it to include the email from the domain urfu.me.</span></p>
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>Mark that you are a student of Ural Federal University. Click on the «Сохранить». Registration on the platform is complete.</p>
                    <img src="openedu/3.png" width="400">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div id="2p" class="text 2t">
                <h1>Course enrollment</h1>
                <p>To enroll in a course, use the course catalog; if the table does not indicate that enrollment is done by the partner institution's staff, you must enroll in the online course yourself.
                    <span class="bold">!If this information is present, you do not need to enroll yourself! If after a few weeks from the start of the course you still have not been added to the group, please send an email to <a href = "openedu@urfu.ru">openedu@urfu.ru</a>. Enter your full name, group number, university, e-mail and course name. Don't forget to describe the problem you are having.</span>
                </p>
                <h3>First method</h3>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>You can enroll in a course through the course catalog by clicking on the link next to the course title. On the page that opens, click on the button «Записаться».</p>
                    <img src="openedu/4.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <h3>Second method</h3>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>You can also use the convenient search engine on the website to enroll in your chosen course <a href = "openedu.ru">openedu.ru</a>.</p>
                    <img src="openedu/5.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <img src="openedu/6.png" width="400">
                    <p>Choose the right course.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>On the page that opens, click on «Записаться».</p>
                    <img src="openedu/7.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <p class="bold">!Please note that the enrollment period for the course and some assignments are limited, so you must enroll during the first week of the semester to complete all assignments and receive credit for the course! Once enrollment is complete, the course will not be available to add new students.
                    If you can't find the course you are looking for or have trouble registering, send an email to <a href = "openedu@urfu.ru">openedu@urfu.ru</a>. In your letter, please provide your full name, group number, university, e-mail and course title. Don't forget to describe the problem you are having.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div id="3p" class="text 3t">
                <h1>Progress Tracking</h1>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>Press the button «Мой профиль», then go to «Мои курсы».</p>
                    <img src="openedu/8.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <img src="openedu/9.png" width="400">
                    <p>Click on the button «Перейти к материалам курса». <span class="bold">Click on the button «Перейти к материалам курса».
                        !Please note, once you have enrolled in the course, the technical support staff will add you to the correct group. You will then have access to all course materials except for the final control! If this group is not listed, you should send an e-mail to the following address <a href = "openedu@urfu.ru">openedu@urfu.ru</a>. In your letter please specify your full name, academic group, course name, mail with which you are registered on openedu.ru and description of the problem!
                        </span>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>During the course you will study the lecture material, complete the assessment tasks and pass the final control (proctoring).</p>
                    <img src="openedu/10.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <img src="openedu/11.png" width="400">
                    <p>Remember that there is a time limit for completing the assessment tasks. This means that by the closing date of the assignments indicated on the page «График открытия материалов», you must have a score of at least 40% on each type of assignment in the column «Оценка».
                        Once the deadline has passed, the assignments will not be available. You can check the number of points that you have earned in the section «Прогресс».
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>If you have any questions while studying the online course, you can always ask them in the following section «Обсуждения». Formulate the question in detail, identifying the section, topic, and unit of the course in which the question arose.</p>
                    <img src="openedu/12.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <p>The final course grade is made up of three components: course progress, exam score, and proctoring status. The proctoring status can be found on the «Прогресс».</p>
            </div>
            <div id="4p" class="text 4t">
                <h1>Final testing</h1>
                <p>The deadlines for the final control are determined by the order for the session. The schedule of examinations and the document with the order are published 2 weeks before the online session. <a href = "https://inf-online.urfu.ru/ru/grafik-ehkzamenov/">Schedule of examinations</a>.</p>
                <h3>Final testing on the courses of partner universities</h3>
                <ol>
                    <ul><a href ="https://openedu.ru/proctoring-rules-itmoproctor/">Instruction</a> on passing the ITMO course evaluations.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/fileadmin/user_upload/site_21245/manual/Instrukcija_MGU_vesna_2022.docx">Instruction</a> on passing the MSU course evaluations.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/fileadmin/user_upload/site_21245/manual/Examus_Instrukcija_Asinkhronnyi_proktoring.pdf">Instruction</a> on passing the certification of MISIS courses.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://openedu.ru/proctoring-manual-itmoproctor/">Instruction</a> on passing the MIFI course evaluations.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/fileadmin/user_upload/site_21245/manual/Examus_Instrukcija_Asinkhronnyi_proktoring.pdf">Instruction</a> on passing the MIPT course evaluations.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://elearning.hse.ru/examsertsforuni">Instruction</a> on passing the certification on the courses of the National Research University Higher School of Economics.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://openedu.ru/proctoring-manual-itmoproctor/">Instruction</a> on passing the certification of SPbPU (Politech) courses.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/fileadmin/user_upload/site_21245/manual/examus_spbgu.pdf">Instruction</a> on passing the SPbU course evaluations.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/fileadmin/user_upload/site_21245/manual/examus_async_tumgu.pdf">Instruction</a> on passing the certification of TyumSU courses.</ul>
                    <ul><a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/fileadmin/user_upload/site_21245/manual/Instrukcija_TGU_asinkhron.pdf">Instruction</a> on passing the TSU course evaluations.</ul>
                </ol>
                <h3>Final Controls for UrFU Courses</h3>
                <p>To successfully pass the final test, you need to install the latest version of the ITMOproctor application and read the following instructions:</p>
                <p>Application link: <a href="https://itmoproctor.openedu.ru/dist/">youk!</a>;</p>
                <p>Link to instructions: <a href="https://openedu.ru/proctoring-manual-itmoproctor/">youk!</a>;</p>
                <p><a href="https://vk.com/video-196169577_456239027">Video instruction</a> of UrFU's final control records.</p>
                <h5>To successfully pass the final test, you need to know the following:</h5>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>Before you start training, make sure you do not belong to a group of “по умолчанию”. Information about your group is available in the course card on the website <a href="http://openedu.ru/">openedu.ru</a> under “Мои курсы”.</p>
                    <img src="openedu/13.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <img src="openedu/14.png" width="400">
                    <p>Make sure the deadline for final testing for your course has not yet passed.<a href="https://inf-online.urfu.ru/ru/grafik-ehkzamenov/">Schedule of examinations</a>. UrFU students must pass the “Final Control (UrFU)».</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <p>The number of slots for test enrollment is limited. There are no additional slots or extensions of the deadlines for the final control within the session.
                        <span class="bold">!The number of slots for test enrollment is limited.!Keep the record for the last few days!</span> When you sign up for a slot, the ITMOproctor app shows the local time based on your location. If you have changed the time on your computer and now it does not match your local time, you should refer to the time displayed in the lower left corner of the ITMOproctor app. Recording and submission takes place in accordance with it.</p>
                    <img src="openedu/15.png" width="400">
                </div>
                <div class="pict">
                    <img src="openedu/16.png" width="400">
                    <p>Before starting the final test, make sure your webcam and microphone are working correctly. Check the video and sound quality in the ITMOproctor app (click on the “Проверка” in the interface menu). Your voice should be clear and your face should be recognizable in the video. <span class="bold">!In case your microphone is part of a headset, DO NOT wear headphones during the Final Exam!</span></p>
                </div>
                <div class="proctorinfo">
                    <p>Check your personal information in<a href="https://sso.openedu.ru/realms/openedu/account/">profile</a>. They must match the data on the student ID card. ITMOproctor will need to take a photo of the document (student ID card) or upload a photo of the document taken in advance.</p>
                    <p>Please note that your profile must include the student's corporate email address in the domain @urfu.me. If a different mailing address is provided, no grade will be given for the exam or the course as a whole.</p>
                    <p>During the workspace demonstration:
                        <ol>
                            <ul>Show the surface on which your computer or laptop sits.</ul>
                            <ul>Use a mirror to showcase your computer screen and the space around it.</ul>
                            <ul>If there is a second monitor, show that it is disconnected from the computer and turned off.</ul>
                            <ul>Space around the workplace to make sure there are no unauthorized people.</ul>
                            <ul>If the camera is built in, it is possible to use a mirror that can be used to show the surroundings.</ul>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                    <p>The exam is administered in asynchronous mode. Test verification may take up to 5 working days.
                        If it is not technically possible to take the final control from home, you should contact the directorate of your institute in advance with a request to provide a workplace that meets the conditions for passing the proctoring.
                    </p>
                    <p>Please note:
                        <ol>
                            <ul>It is the student's responsibility not to leave the webcam's line of sight during tests.</ul>
                            <ul>The microphone shall not be switched off during the test and its sensitivity shall be within normal limits.</ul>
                            <ul>The student may not enlist the assistance of third parties during testing.</ul>
                            <ul>The student may not give access to the computer to outside parties during testing. All programs capable of recording and broadcasting what is happening on the desktop must be turned off.</ul>
                            <ul>The student is not allowed to: engage in conversations with third parties, speak questions aloud, use reference materials (books, cheat sheets, notes, course materials not on the test page), use cell phones, pagers, calculators, tablets, headphones, check answers against progress changes during testing.</ul>
                            <ul>The student agrees that systematic averting of the gaze to the edge of the monitor/beyond the screen may be considered the use of supplemental materials.</ul>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                    <p>Students are allowed:
                        <ol>
                            <ul>Use only the computer on which the test is being taken.</ul>
                            <ul>When taking tests in technical subjects, use the engineering calculator built into the operating system (Start > Calculator).</ul>
                            <ul>If the course allows the use of a draft, you must demonstrate on camera that it is clean before the exam. At the end of the exam, that no final control questions have been written on the rough draft.</ul>
                            <ul>If the headset is used as a microphone, headphones must not be worn. The turned on headset must be placed on the desk next to the keyboard.</ul>
                            <ul>International students are allowed the use of an interpreter (only <a href="translate.google.com">translate.google.com</a> or <a href="translate.yandex.ru">translate.yandex.ru</a>) on the adjacent tab during the final control.</ul>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                    <p>If the test is rejected by the proctor, the user has the right to request an additional attempt to take the final control.</p>
                    <p class="bold">!In case violations of the rules described above are detected, the attempt is considered used and the test is considered unsuccessful!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
